reviews.review_text: DSO at the Fillmore 2009-10-04 What a fun show!  I am sure the original was quite wonderful, however I was only 6 at the time.  Lotsa room to dance and I did.  During Peggy-O I was front stage right and was spinning the entire song, delightful.  Eyes, always gets me.  For the third verse I had to stop dancing and hold the rail at stage left.  "Sometimes the songs that we hear are just songs of our own."  That always gets me Farklempt,  Anyways, this note you just read, and I just wrote, wasn't a review of the *Grateful Dead's* performance, merely of the set list and Dark Star Orchestra's interpretation thereof.  I look forward to hearing the genuine article!
